HEADWORD: Designator
<hw>Des"ig*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An officer who assigned to
each his rank and place in public shows and ceremonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who designates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Designatory</ent>⟦br⟧
